YEAH, BUT THEY'RE
NOT MY ROOTS.

10:57.850 --> 10:59.850
THEY'RE MY WIFE'S ROOTS.

10:59.890 --> 11:01.190
WHEN SHAUNA PASSED,
I TRIED

11:01.220 --> 11:03.920
TO MAKE THIS PLACE
HOME AND...

11:03.960 --> 11:06.330
IT WAS,
FOR A LONG TIME.

11:06.360 --> 11:07.730
I MEAN, YOU KNOW,
WOOD, I --

11:07.760 --> 11:09.260
I LOVE SAINT JO'S.

11:09.300 --> 11:12.870
BUT EVERYTHING
WITH CHARLEY AND NOVA

11:12.900 --> 11:16.570
SHOWED ME
WHO I REALLY AM.

11:16.610 --> 11:18.340
AND I DON'T LIKE
WHAT I SEE.

11:18.370 --> 11:20.040
YOU'RE A GOOD MAN,
REMY.

11:20.080 --> 11:21.140
DON'T DO THIS
TO YOURSELF.

11:21.180 --> 11:22.180
[ SIGH ]

11:22.210 --> 11:25.080
I JUST HAVE THIS LACK
INSIDE OF ME

11:25.110 --> 11:27.250
THAT I ALWAYS HAVE
TO FILL BECAUSE...

11:27.280 --> 11:28.310
LIFE DIDN'T HAPPEN

11:28.350 --> 11:30.050
THE WAY I PLANNED
FOR MYSELF.

11:30.090 --> 11:35.060
YOU KNOW, A WIFE, KIDS,
HAPPILY EVER AFTER.

11:35.090 --> 11:36.690
AND THAT AFFECTED ME

11:36.730 --> 11:39.290
AND I GOTTA
ADMIT IT.

11:39.330 --> 11:42.130
I HEAR YA.

11:42.160 --> 11:45.270
I REALLY WANTED CHARLEY
TO BE THE ONE.

11:45.300 --> 11:48.270
BUT, WHEN WE BROKE UP,
IT DEVASTATED ME,

11:48.300 --> 11:51.170
'CAUSE I DIDN'T THINK I WAS
EVER GONNA FIND LOVE AGAIN.

11:51.210 --> 11:54.140
AND THEN, FEELINGS
STARTED TO DEVELOP

11:54.180 --> 11:56.310
BETWEEN ME AND NOVA AND...

11:56.340 --> 12:00.010
[ JUKEBOX PLAYS
ROMANTIC BALLAD ]

12:00.050 --> 12:01.920
SUDDENLY,
I FELT HOPE AGAIN.

12:01.950 --> 12:04.350
♪♪

12:04.390 --> 12:06.890
FUNNY THING IS,

12:06.920 --> 12:08.960
THINK THE TWO OF<i> YOU</i>
WOULDA MADE A GOOD COUPLE.

12:08.990 --> 12:11.020
I AIN'T GONNA NEVER TELL
VI OR NOBODY ELSE THAT,

12:11.060 --> 12:13.590
BUT, Y'ALL MATCH.

12:13.630 --> 12:15.130
BOTH OF Y'ALL
SMART AS HELL.

12:15.160 --> 12:17.300
YOU LOVE
YOUR COMMUNITY.

12:17.330 --> 12:19.400
I THINK IT COULDA
WORKED OUT.

12:19.430 --> 12:21.500
YEAH, WELL,

12:21.540 --> 12:23.770
NOTHING WORKED.

12:23.810 --> 12:25.940
NOTHING'S WORKING HERE.

12:25.970 --> 12:30.480
I GOTTA GO STAND
ON MY OWN

12:30.510 --> 12:32.110
AND FIND MYSELF AGAIN.

12:32.150 --> 12:34.950
♪♪

12:34.980 --> 12:36.380
ALRIGHT!

12:36.420 --> 12:38.220
GOODIES
FOR THE ROAD.

12:38.250 --> 12:39.690
THANK YOU.

12:39.720 --> 12:41.650
YOU TAKE CARE
OF YOURSELF, REMY.

12:41.690 --> 12:43.490
AND DON'T BE
A STRANGER.

12:43.530 --> 12:45.390
ERNEST<i> LOVED</i> YOU.

12:45.430 --> 12:47.090
YOU'RE A PART OF US.

12:47.130 --> 12:48.390
SO,
DON'T FORGET US,

12:48.430 --> 12:50.100
'CAUSE WE NOT
ABOUT TO FORGET YOU.

12:50.130 --> 12:52.930
♪♪

12:52.970 --> 12:55.340
THANKS, VI.

12:55.370 --> 13:01.240
♪♪

13:01.280 --> 13:05.040
-♪<i> TURN BACK TO ME</i> ♪
-GOD BLESS YOU, MY BROTHER.

13:05.080 --> 13:06.980
-♪<i> OR JUST SET ME</i> ♪
-BLESS YOU, TOO, MAN.

13:07.020 --> 13:13.490
♪<i> FREE</i> ♪

13:13.520 --> 13:15.620
♪♪

13:15.660 --> 13:18.160
AYE, UH...

13:18.190 --> 13:20.360
TELL 'EM BOTH I SAID

13:20.400 --> 13:22.160
GOODBYE
AND THANK YOU.

13:22.200 --> 13:32.170
♪♪

13:32.210 --> 13:34.740
♪♪

13:34.780 --> 13:38.280
[ DOOR OPENS ]

13:38.310 --> 13:41.380
[ OUTRO PLAYS ]
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

13:41.420 --> 13:43.920
[<i> CHIME</i> ]

13:43.950 --> 13:48.090
[<i> VOICE OVER PA</i> ]

13:48.120 --> 13:50.790
[ BUZZ ]

13:50.830 --> 13:54.030
[ SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYS ]

13:54.060 --> 13:55.230
YOU GOT 10 MINUTES.

13:55.260 --> 13:57.300
♪♪

13:57.330 --> 13:58.400
WHAT'S UP?

13:58.430 --> 14:07.210
♪♪

14:07.240 --> 14:08.040
♪♪

14:08.080 --> 14:09.580
LIKE THE HAIR.

14:09.610 --> 14:12.180
-THANKS.
-IT'S COOL.

14:12.210 --> 14:15.110
I SEE I'M NOT THE ONLY
ONE WITH A NEW LOOK.

14:15.150 --> 14:17.680
YEAH, ASHA GAVE IT TO ME
OVER THE SUMMER,

14:17.720 --> 14:19.990
RIGHT BEFORE
I REPORTED HERE.

14:20.020 --> 14:22.720
GOT THE IDEA FROM
MAYA ANGELOU'S POEM.

14:22.760 --> 14:24.560
THAT'S REALLY DOPE.

14:24.590 --> 14:26.230
HELPS ME KEEP MY HEAD UP.

14:26.260 --> 14:29.560
YOU KNOW,
WHEN I'M DOWN.

14:29.600 --> 14:32.670
HOW YOU HOLDING UP
IN HERE?

14:32.700 --> 14:35.970
I'M A'IGHT, I GUESS.

14:36.000 --> 14:40.310
READING A LOT,
DRAWING.

14:40.340 --> 14:42.580
IT'S COOL, THOUGH.

14:42.610 --> 14:43.910
YEAH?

14:46.750 --> 14:50.220
I'M YOUR FRIEND, MAN.
YOU COULD...

14:50.250 --> 14:52.120
TELL ME HOW THINGS
REALLY ARE IN HERE.

14:52.150 --> 14:54.290
[ MELANCHOLY TUNE PLAYS ]

14:54.320 --> 14:55.660
YEAH, LOOK, THE ONLY THING
THAT MATTERS IS

14:55.690 --> 14:58.120
THAT I KEEP MY HEAD DOWN

14:58.160 --> 15:00.790
AND DO MY TIME

15:00.830 --> 15:02.730
AND DO WHATEVER I CAN
TO NEVER COME BACK.

15:02.760 --> 15:07.100
♪♪

15:07.140 --> 15:08.770
WE WERE TRYING TO DO
SOMETHING GOOD...

15:08.800 --> 15:11.100
♪♪

15:11.140 --> 15:15.110
WAKE FOLK UP
AROUND HERE, BUT...

15:15.140 --> 15:17.480
I DON'T KNOW,
MAN, JUST...

15:17.510 --> 15:18.540
I DON'T FEEL LIKE
IT WAS WORTH IT.

15:18.580 --> 15:20.210
DON'T DO THAT,
BRUH.

15:20.250 --> 15:22.220
I'M GLAD TO SEE YOU,

15:22.250 --> 15:23.480
BUT YOU CAN'T
JUST COME TELL ME

15:23.520 --> 15:26.990
THE REASON I'M IN HERE
WASN'T WORTH IT.

15:27.020 --> 15:29.390
IT HAD TO BE.

15:29.420 --> 15:31.590
LOOK, I CAN'T GET THROUGH THIS
THINKING LIKE THAT, MAN.

15:31.630 --> 15:35.090
I DIDN'T MEAN IT
LIKE THAT.

15:35.130 --> 15:37.630
I'M SORRY, ANT.

15:37.670 --> 15:38.770
I AM.

15:38.800 --> 15:40.800
♪♪

15:40.840 --> 15:42.670
[<i> VOICE OVER PA,</i>
<i> RADIO CHATTER</i> ]

15:42.700 --> 15:44.170
I WAS MOVIN' ON.

15:44.210 --> 15:45.970
NEW CITY, NEW CAREER.

15:46.010 --> 15:47.440
NOVA'S BOOK
COMES OUT.

15:47.480 --> 15:49.810
YOUR PROBLEMS AREN'T
ABOUT NOVA.

15:49.840 --> 15:51.810
YOU TOOK A JOB
AT A UNIVERSITY,

15:51.850 --> 15:55.080
WHERE EMPLOYEES ARE HELD
TO A HIGHER STANDARD THAN...

15:55.120 --> 15:57.520
NBA AFTER-PARTIES.

15:57.550 --> 15:58.890
YEAH, WELL,

15:58.920 --> 16:00.590
WHATEVER IT IS,
I DON'T LIKE IT.

16:00.620 --> 16:02.260
IT'S CALLED EQUAL
TREATMENT, DAVIS.

16:02.290 --> 16:03.360
IT FEELS LIKE
OPPRESSION TO YOU

16:03.390 --> 16:04.860
BECAUSE YOU'RE USED
TO PRIVILEGE.

16:08.160 --> 16:09.460
[ SIGH ]

16:09.500 --> 16:11.230
LOOK,

16:11.270 --> 16:14.300
I KNOW THAT
I'VE BEEN PRIVILEGED

16:14.340 --> 16:15.600
AND CODDLED
AND PROTECTED

16:15.640 --> 16:17.540
AND ALL OF THAT,
OKAY?

16:17.570 --> 16:20.870
AND YOU, CHARLEY,
YOU GAVE ME THE WORLD.

16:20.910 --> 16:23.210
AND I BLEW IT.
I KNOW THAT.

16:23.240 --> 16:24.710
BUT WHAT I TOOK
FOR GRANTED THEN,

16:24.750 --> 16:25.710
I'M BEGGIN' YOU
FOR NOW.

16:25.750 --> 16:28.380
SO, CHARLEY, PLEASE,
DO SOMETHIN'.

16:28.420 --> 16:29.720
LOOK, YESTERDAY,
THERE WERE

16:29.750 --> 16:31.350
ONLY 10 PROTESTERS
OUTSIDE THE GYM.

16:31.390 --> 16:32.850
TODAY, 200.

16:32.890 --> 16:34.150
AND, IF THIS GETS
ANY WORSE,

16:34.190 --> 16:35.220
THEN BAYOU STATE'LL
HAVE NO CHOICE

16:35.260 --> 16:36.460
BUT TO GET RID OF ME.

16:36.490 --> 16:38.020
I NEED THIS.

16:38.060 --> 16:39.230
THEN BE HONEST.

16:39.260 --> 16:40.390
DO SOME INTERVIEWS

16:40.430 --> 16:44.260
AND TAKE RESPONSIBILITY
FOR YOUR MISTAKES.

16:44.300 --> 16:45.300
THE PUBLIC MIGHT GIVE YOU

16:45.330 --> 16:46.730
A SECOND SHOT.
MIGHT?

16:46.770 --> 16:48.530
IF YOU'RE LOOKING
FOR GUARANTEES, DAVIS,

16:48.570 --> 16:49.770
THEN YOU SHOULDA
KEPT IT IN YOUR PANTS,

16:49.800 --> 16:52.070
IN THE FIRST PLACE.

16:52.110 --> 16:55.070
DO YOU EVEN<i> UNDERSTAND</i>
WHAT YOU DID?

16:55.110 --> 16:57.440
NOT TO ME.

16:57.480 --> 16:58.510
TO HER.

16:58.550 --> 17:01.850
[ SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYS ]

17:01.880 --> 17:03.680
OWN YOUR MISTAKES.

17:03.720 --> 17:07.650
THEN, MAYBE, THERE<i> MIGHT</i>
BE A SMALL CHANCE

17:07.690 --> 17:09.660
THE STORY WILL DIE OUT
IN A FEW DAYS.

17:09.690 --> 17:12.090
♪♪

17:12.130 --> 17:14.090
I BELIEVE YOU,
CHARLEY.

17:14.130 --> 17:16.300
I BELIEVE<i> IN</i> YOU.

17:16.330 --> 17:17.430
ALWAYS HAVE.

17:17.470 --> 17:20.570
♪♪

17:20.600 --> 17:22.340
EVEN WHEN I DON'T LIKE
WHAT YOU'RE SAYIN'.

17:24.870 --> 17:28.140
[<i> ROMANTIC JAZZ PLAYS</i> ]

17:28.180 --> 17:30.780
HELLO.

17:30.810 --> 17:31.840
OCTAVIA.

17:31.880 --> 17:34.710
NOVA. WHAT A NICE
SURPRISE.

17:34.750 --> 17:37.620
BUT THEN, YOU ALWAYS
DID HAVE GREAT TIMING.

17:37.650 --> 17:39.590
LET'S SEE IF YOU FEEL
THAT WAY AFTER I BLAST YOU

17:39.620 --> 17:41.920
FOR THAT STUNT
YOU PULLED AT MY Q&A.

17:41.960 --> 17:43.120
HOLD THAT THOUGHT.

17:43.160 --> 17:44.620
WE WERE JUST ABOUT
TO DISCUSS YOUR BOOK

17:44.660 --> 17:46.230
FOR THIS WEEK'S
SEMINAR.

17:46.260 --> 17:49.130
THE STUDENTS<i> REALLY</i>
LOVED YOUR TALK.

17:49.160 --> 17:50.700
WOULD YOU LIKE
TO JOIN IS?

17:50.730 --> 17:52.130
MY BOOK?

17:52.170 --> 17:54.200
OH, I GET IT NOW.

17:54.240 --> 17:56.000
I'VE BEEN OCTAVIA'D.

17:56.040 --> 17:58.100
YOU GOAD ME AT MY EVENT,
KNOWING I'D RESPOND

17:58.140 --> 18:01.110
AND HERE YOU ARE,
<i> WAITING</i> FOR ME.

18:01.140 --> 18:02.540
IT'S CUTE.

18:02.580 --> 18:05.140
BUT I WANT NO PART
OF YOUR GAMES, OCTAVIA.

18:05.180 --> 18:07.010
THE NOVA BORDELON
I REMEMBER

18:07.050 --> 18:09.120
NEVER BACKED DOWN
FROM A CHALLENGE,

18:09.150 --> 18:11.150
ESPECIALLY IF IT
CAME FROM ME.

18:11.190 --> 18:18.960
♪♪

18:18.990 --> 18:22.260
NEVER HAD SOMEONE PACK ME
A PICNIC BASKET BEFORE.

18:22.300 --> 18:23.500
[ CHUCKLE ]

18:23.530 --> 18:24.700
AND I DON'T THINK

18:24.730 --> 18:27.230
I'VE BEEN ON A PICNIC
SINCE I WAS A KID.

18:27.270 --> 18:28.230
YEAH.

18:28.270 --> 18:31.140
IT'S BEEN A MINUTE
FOR ME, TOO.

18:31.170 --> 18:33.870
IT'S MY FIRST TIME
WITHOUT THE KIDS.

18:33.910 --> 18:37.440
I WANTED TO, UH,
MARK THE OCCASION.

18:37.480 --> 18:41.850
[ TENDER TUNE PLAYS ]

18:41.880 --> 18:44.080
GOT THESE FOR YOU.

18:44.120 --> 18:46.150
DIDN'T KNOW YOU WERE
SUCH A ROMANTIC.

18:46.190 --> 18:47.550
[ LAUGHTER ]

18:47.590 --> 18:49.020
I DIDN'T KNOW,
EITHER.

18:49.060 --> 18:52.120
♪♪

18:52.160 --> 18:54.690
FOLKS WITHOUT KIDS
DON'T EVEN KNOW.

18:54.730 --> 18:56.660
THE STRUGGLE IS REAL.

18:56.700 --> 19:03.740
♪♪

19:03.770 --> 19:05.300
[ BELL RINGS ]

19:05.340 --> 19:08.410
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

19:08.440 --> 19:10.880
UGH! OH.

19:10.910 --> 19:12.210
HERE YOU GO,
BLUE.

19:12.250 --> 19:13.950
CONGRATULATIONS
ON WINNING
THE SPELLING BEE.

19:13.980 --> 19:15.620
THANKS, MARCUS.

19:15.650 --> 19:17.850
I STUDIED REALLY HARD
WITH MY DADDY.

19:17.890 --> 19:19.290
OH. BUT,

19:19.320 --> 19:22.520
MY MOM SAYS YOU AIN'T
GOT A DADDY.

19:22.560 --> 19:23.760
WHAT?

19:23.790 --> 19:25.830
WHAT, MY POPS<i> IS</i>
MY DADDY.

19:25.860 --> 19:28.160
BUT SHE SAYS HE AIN'T
YOUR REAL ONE.

19:28.200 --> 19:29.700
I HEARD HER TELL
MY AUNTIE

19:29.730 --> 19:31.000
YOU AIN'T GOT
NO REAL DADDY,

19:31.030 --> 19:32.600
WHILE THEY WAS
ON THE PHONE.

19:32.630 --> 19:34.570
♪♪

19:34.600 --> 19:36.170
WANNA GO PLAY
ON THE SWINGS?

19:36.200 --> 19:37.700
♪♪

19:39.710 --> 19:41.040
YOUR AUNT IS LEGIT

19:41.080 --> 19:44.040
A FULL-ON CHEF
AND MIRACLE WORKER.

19:44.080 --> 19:46.810
AND YOU GREW UP WITH THIS
KIND OF FOOD DAILY?

19:46.850 --> 19:48.450
ALL DAY.

19:48.480 --> 19:51.550
MY DADDY COULDN'T COOK,
SO AUNT VI KEPT US FED.

19:51.590 --> 19:53.890
KEPT US FED
GOOD, TOO.

19:53.920 --> 19:55.190
SHE SURE DID.

19:55.220 --> 19:57.790
YEAH.

19:57.830 --> 19:59.690
SHE TEACH YOU HOW?

19:59.730 --> 20:01.760
[chuckling]
WHAT, TO COOK?

20:01.800 --> 20:02.760
YEAH, I COULD BURN.

20:02.800 --> 20:04.200
-WHA-A-T?!
-YEAH.

20:04.230 --> 20:05.930
[ LAUGHTER ]

20:05.970 --> 20:07.430
OH, WAIT.

20:07.470 --> 20:10.140
THERE'S SOME REAL BOASTIN'
AND BRAGGING GOIN' ON,

20:10.170 --> 20:11.900
BUT DO YOU HAVE THE CHOPS
TO BACK IT UP,

20:11.940 --> 20:14.140
IS WHAT I'M TRYING
TO KNOW.

20:14.180 --> 20:15.640
I MEAN,
YOU COULD FIND OUT.

20:15.680 --> 20:16.980
[ TENDER TUNE PLAYS ]

20:17.010 --> 20:18.210
[ LAUGHS ]

20:18.250 --> 20:20.010
FIND OUT A LOTTA
THINGS, REALLY.

20:20.050 --> 20:27.550
♪♪

20:27.590 --> 20:29.620
[ BUZZ ]

20:29.660 --> 20:31.420
[ BUZZ ]

20:31.460 --> 20:33.660
[ SIGH ]
[ BUZZ ]

20:33.700 --> 20:34.960
THE SOONER YOU ANSWER IT,

20:35.000 --> 20:38.800
THE SOONER WE CAN START
OUR SECOND KISS.

20:38.830 --> 20:40.000
HELLO.

20:41.170 --> 20:45.140
[ SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYS ]

20:45.170 --> 20:48.040
NAH, I UNDERSTAND.

20:48.080 --> 20:50.940
EVERYTHING ALRIGHT?

20:50.980 --> 20:53.880
A'IGHT.

20:53.920 --> 20:55.150
I GOTTA GO.

20:55.180 --> 20:57.950
IT'S BLUE.

20:57.990 --> 21:01.150
THANKS FOR TAKING THE
TIME OUT TO HELP ME.

21:01.190 --> 21:03.020
YOU KNOW, IT FELT
A LITTLE LIKE OLD TIMES.

21:03.060 --> 21:04.620
YOU AND ME
AGAINST THE WORLD,

21:04.660 --> 21:07.030
SOLVIN' PROBLEMS.

21:07.060 --> 21:08.590
YEAH, I GUESS IT DID.

21:08.630 --> 21:10.260
WELL.

21:10.300 --> 21:11.560
BIGGEST REGRET
I HAVE IS THAT,

21:11.600 --> 21:16.540
WHEN THINGS WENT BAD
BETWEEN US,

21:16.570 --> 21:17.870
I DIDN'T FIGHT
HARD ENOUGH FOR YOU.

21:17.910 --> 21:20.110
[ MELANCHOLY TUNE PLAYS ]

21:20.140 --> 21:21.440
[ SIGH ]

21:21.480 --> 21:22.940
THERE WAS A TIME

21:22.980 --> 21:25.340
WHEN I<i> REALLY</i> NEEDED
TO HEAR THOSE WORDS...

21:25.380 --> 21:28.250
♪♪

21:28.280 --> 21:29.380
...MORE THAN ANYTHING.

21:29.420 --> 21:34.320
♪♪

21:34.360 --> 21:35.450
[ CHUCKLE ]

21:35.490 --> 21:40.860
♪♪

21:40.900 --> 21:43.260
THAT TIME IS GONE.

21:43.300 --> 21:45.670
DAVIS,
YOU'RE STILL LYING.

21:45.700 --> 21:47.230
I JUST FOUND OUT
A FEW MONTHS AGO

21:47.270 --> 21:50.640
THAT YOU HAVE
A WHOLE OTHER FAMILY.

21:50.670 --> 21:53.170
LOOK, WE'RE FINALLY AT A PLACE
WHERE WE CAN SIT AT A TABLE

21:53.210 --> 21:55.110
AND NOT TEAR
EACH OTHER APART.

21:55.140 --> 21:57.310
♪♪

21:57.350 --> 21:59.310
LET'S JUST

21:59.350 --> 22:01.050
LET THAT BE ENOUGH.

22:01.080 --> 22:03.650
BECAUSE, FOR ME,
THERE'S NO MORE.

22:03.690 --> 22:07.090
♪♪

22:07.120 --> 22:11.260
WELL, THAT'S OUR FIRST
FUNERAL WE'VE CATERED.

22:11.290 --> 22:13.060
I KNOW,
AND I HATE IT.

22:13.090 --> 22:15.560
ME, TOO.
[chuckling]

22:15.600 --> 22:17.200
BUT I'M GLAD
THEY CALLED US.

22:17.230 --> 22:19.870
GIRL, YOU GONNA GET
EVERY REPAST AND BIRTHDAY

22:19.900 --> 22:22.470
AND EVERYTHING IN BETWEEN
FOR A LONG AS YOU WANT.

22:25.470 --> 22:27.410
WELL, I'LL TAKE IT,

22:27.440 --> 22:30.180
LONG AS YOU WITH ME.

22:30.210 --> 22:32.110
WHAT'S WRONG, BABY?

22:32.150 --> 22:34.750
♪♪

22:34.780 --> 22:38.450
I'M SCARED ALL OVER AGAIN.

22:38.490 --> 22:41.450
TOOK SO MANY YEARS TO

22:41.490 --> 22:44.460
GET OVER THIS FEELING
AND, NOW, IT'S BACK.

22:44.490 --> 22:45.460
BABY, YOU KNOW
I AIN'T GONNA LET

22:45.490 --> 22:46.560
NOTHIN' HAPPEN TO YOU.

22:46.590 --> 22:50.460
♪♪

22:50.500 --> 22:51.660
BUT IT AIN'T LIKE THAT.

22:51.700 --> 22:55.170
♪♪

22:55.200 --> 22:56.340
I CAN'T EXPLAIN IT.

22:56.370 --> 23:00.740
♪♪

23:00.780 --> 23:01.810
TRY.

23:01.840 --> 23:05.140
♪♪

23:05.180 --> 23:06.210
IT'S IN ME.

23:06.250 --> 23:09.250
♪♪

23:09.280 --> 23:12.420
THE WAY HE TREATED ME,

23:12.450 --> 23:13.650
HOW I USED TO LIVE,

23:13.690 --> 23:20.360
HOW I USED TO BE,
THE FEAR.

23:20.390 --> 23:21.730
IT'S STILL IN ME.

23:21.760 --> 23:26.670
♪♪

23:26.700 --> 23:28.400
AND YOU CAN'T
PROTECT ME FROM THAT.

23:28.440 --> 23:31.900
♪♪

23:31.940 --> 23:34.510
YOU RIGHT.

23:34.540 --> 23:38.540
I CAN'T PROTECT YOU FROM
WHAT YOU FEELING INSIDE.

23:38.580 --> 23:40.410
BUT WHAT I CAN DO
IS BE RIGHT HERE WITH YOU

23:40.450 --> 23:42.280
WHILE YOU'RE GOIN'
THROUGH IT.

23:42.320 --> 23:43.620
YOU AIN'T GOTTA GO
THROUGH THIS ALONE.

23:43.650 --> 23:45.450
HELL, YOU SHOULDN'T HAVE
TO GO THROUGH IT AT ALL.

23:45.490 --> 23:48.850
WELL, THAT'S NOVA'S DOING.

23:48.890 --> 23:51.590
I MEAN, AFTER ALL I
DONE FOR HER

23:51.630 --> 23:55.730
SINCE SHE WAS A GIRL,
SINCE TRUDY PASSED.

23:55.760 --> 23:57.500
I WAS THERE EVERY DAY.

23:57.530 --> 24:01.200
SHOWED UP FOR THOSE KIDS,
DID THE RIGHT THING.

24:01.240 --> 24:03.170
SHE SPIT IN MY FACE.

24:03.200 --> 24:04.640
♪♪

24:04.670 --> 24:06.810
I'M NEVER GONNA
FORGIVE HER

24:06.840 --> 24:08.940
FOR BRINGIN' ALL THIS
BACK ON ME.

24:08.980 --> 24:11.710
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

24:11.750 --> 24:13.280
YOUR PROSE IS SHARP
AND OBSERVANT.

24:13.310 --> 24:14.350
THANK YOU.

24:14.380 --> 24:16.050
BUT I FOUND
YOUR METHODOLOGY

24:16.080 --> 24:17.850
IRRELEVANT
<i> AND</i> OUTDATED.

24:17.890 --> 24:19.650
I'M CURIOUS: ARE YOU
FAMILIAR WITH THE WORKS

24:19.690 --> 24:21.550
OF BRITTNEY COOPER,
DR. KEISHA BLAIN,

24:21.590 --> 24:23.790
REBECCA TRAISTER?

24:23.830 --> 24:26.790
YOU KNOW, BRITT AND I
WERE JUST TALKING ABOUT

24:26.830 --> 24:28.330
HOW LONG IT'S BEEN
SINCE WE HUNG OUT

24:28.360 --> 24:30.060
WITH KEISHA AND REBECCA.

24:30.100 --> 24:31.960
NEXT TIME WE GET
TOGETHER FOR LUNCH,

24:32.000 --> 24:33.230
I'LL MAKE SURE
TO ASK THEM

24:33.270 --> 24:37.240
IF<i> THEY</i> THINK
MY METHODS ARE<i> OUTDATED.</i>

24:37.270 --> 24:40.740
WHILE THIS EXCHANGE HAS BEEN
VERY STIMULATING,

24:40.780 --> 24:43.510
MISS BORDELON AND I HAVE
SOME CATCHING UP TO DO.

24:43.540 --> 24:45.440
I WILL SEE YOU ALL
IN SEMINAR ON MONDAY.

24:45.480 --> 24:48.580
[ MELLOW R&B PLAYS ]

24:48.620 --> 24:51.380
♪♪

24:51.420 --> 24:52.650
THAT'LL BE ALL, JASMINE.

24:52.690 --> 25:02.090
♪♪

25:02.130 --> 25:04.000
♪♪

25:04.030 --> 25:07.870
[ LAUGHING ]

25:07.900 --> 25:10.040
I SEE YOU STILL
HAVE A TYPE.

25:10.070 --> 25:11.100
JASMINE?

25:11.140 --> 25:12.440
SHE'S A VERY BRIGHT

25:12.470 --> 25:14.070
AND TALENTED
YOUNG WOMAN.

25:14.110 --> 25:17.180
I BET SHE IS.

25:17.210 --> 25:19.910
ARE YOU STILL A FAN
OF ITALIAN NEGRONIS?

25:19.950 --> 25:26.450
♪♪

25:26.490 --> 25:28.120
BLUE!

25:28.160 --> 25:29.390
BLUE, COME BACK HERE!

25:30.760 --> 25:32.520
PLEASE, TALK TO ME.

25:32.560 --> 25:33.860
[ SLAM ]

25:33.900 --> 25:36.200
[ DOGS BARKING OUTDOORS ]

25:41.240 --> 25:42.700
DARLA.

25:42.740 --> 25:43.740
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

25:43.770 --> 25:45.500
CAME AS SOON
AS I COULD.

25:45.540 --> 25:47.340
WHERE HE AT?
-HE'S IN THE BEDROOM.

25:50.650 --> 25:52.140
-WHAT HAPPENED?
-I DON'T KNOW.

25:52.180 --> 25:54.580
UH, THE ONLY THING
THAT HE WOULD SAY TO ME

25:54.620 --> 25:56.450
THE ENTIRE WAY HERE IS
THAT HIS FRIEND MARCUS

25:56.480 --> 25:57.780
ISN'T BEING
VERY NICE TO HIM.

25:57.820 --> 25:59.420
AND THE SCHOOL SAID
HE'S BEEN CRYING.

25:59.450 --> 26:01.150
-CRYING?
-A LOT.

26:01.190 --> 26:02.960
-ABOUT WHAT?
-I DON'T KNOW. THEY'RE KIDS.

26:02.990 --> 26:04.120
IT COULD BE ANYTHING.

26:04.160 --> 26:05.860
MOST KIDS.
NOT BLUE.

26:05.890 --> 26:07.730
SOMEBODY
SAID SOMETHIN'.

26:07.760 --> 26:12.770
GOD, I<i> HATE</i> THIS.

26:12.800 --> 26:15.200
WE GOT THROUGH IT<i> ALL.</i>

26:15.240 --> 26:16.800
WHY THIS, NOW?!

26:16.840 --> 26:19.810
I<i> CANNOT</i> BELIEVE
THAT SHE WOULD DO THIS.

26:24.250 --> 26:28.650
[ CHILD WAILING ]
[ CONVERSING IN SPANISH ]

26:28.680 --> 26:31.850
[ TENDER TUNE PLAYS ]

26:31.890 --> 26:36.060
♪♪

26:36.090 --> 26:38.320
<i>LA MEDICINA VA A AYUDAR</i>
<i>CON LA INFECCIóN DEL OíDO</i>

26:38.360 --> 26:39.460
<i> EN UNOS DíAS.</i>

26:39.490 --> 26:40.930
<i> ASEGúRASE QUE TOME</i>
<i> BASTANTE AGUA</i>

26:40.960 --> 26:42.030
<i> Y QUE DUERMA</i>
<i> OCHO HORAS.</i>

26:42.060 --> 26:43.600
♪♪

26:43.630 --> 26:45.660
DANTE, I KNOW THAT SHOT
SCARED YOU, BUT,

26:45.700 --> 26:47.270
YOU WERE VERY BRAVE.

26:47.300 --> 26:48.270
<i> Sí, YO Sé.</i>

26:48.300 --> 26:49.670
GRACIAS.
-IGNACIO.

26:49.700 --> 26:52.570
[ LAUGHING ]

26:52.610 --> 26:55.070
THANK YOU SO MUCH
FOR THIS CLINIC.

26:55.110 --> 26:56.980
SO MANY NEED THIS.

26:57.010 --> 26:58.740
BUT...

26:58.780 --> 27:00.080
THEY'RE JUST SCARED
TO GET HELP.

27:00.110 --> 27:01.710
WELL, WE'RE HERE.

27:01.750 --> 27:02.780
THANK YOU.

27:02.820 --> 27:06.390
<i> ERES UN áNGEL GUARDIáN.</i>

27:06.420 --> 27:08.620
<i> VAMOS.</i>

27:08.660 --> 27:10.020
GUARDIAN ANGEL.

27:10.060 --> 27:11.020
OKAY.

27:11.060 --> 27:12.990
HIGH PRAISE.

27:13.030 --> 27:14.690
I LIKE IT.
-BUT DO YOU AGREE WITH IT?

27:14.730 --> 27:16.400
IMMIGRATION! GET OUT
YOUR PAPERS, NOW!

27:16.430 --> 27:17.430
-IMMIGRATION
-WAIT A MINUTE!

27:17.470 --> 27:18.430
<i> iDOCUMENTACIóN!</i>

27:18.470 --> 27:19.800
-WAIT A MINUTE NO.
-WAIT.

27:19.830 --> 27:21.100
-NO, WAIT.
-MOVE IT, MOVE IT!

27:21.140 --> 27:22.670
YOU CAN'T --
YOU CAN'T DO THIS HERE!

27:22.700 --> 27:24.140
-MOVE OVER!
-THIS ISN'T ALLOWED.

27:24.170 --> 27:25.140
[ CLATTER ]
JUST WAIT A MINUTE.

27:25.170 --> 27:26.210
-BACK OFF!
-STOP! JUST --

27:26.240 --> 27:27.440
-CALM DOWN.
-HOLD ON!

27:27.480 --> 27:28.440
THIS MAKES NO SENSE.
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

27:28.480 --> 27:30.110
REALLY?!<i> REALLY?!</i>

27:30.140 --> 27:31.740
THEY'RE GETTING
MEDICAL ATTENTION.

27:31.780 --> 27:32.950
MA'AM, YOU NEED
TO BACK OFF

27:32.980 --> 27:34.010
AND LET US DO
OUR JOBS.

27:34.050 --> 27:36.150
CLINICS ARE PROTECTED
SPACES. YOU DON'T HAVE

27:36.180 --> 27:37.280
THE AUTHORITY
TO COME IN HERE AND --

27:37.320 --> 27:38.380
YOU WANNA BE ARRESTED
FOR OBSTRUCTION?

27:38.420 --> 27:39.420
-WAIT A -- WAIT A MINUTE.
-EXCUSE ME?

27:39.450 --> 27:40.420
UNDER THE CURRENT
ADMINISTRATION,

27:40.450 --> 27:41.520
ICE HAS ALL THE
AUTHORITY IT NEEDS.

27:41.560 --> 27:42.860
HOW DID YOU HEAR
ABOUT THIS CLINIC?

27:42.890 --> 27:44.490
ANONYMOUS TIP
ABOUT ILLEGAL ALIENS.

27:44.530 --> 27:46.160
"ALIENS"?

27:46.190 --> 27:47.560
THEY'RE PEOPLE.

27:47.600 --> 27:49.430
THEY LIVE HERE, THEY --
THEY HAVE JOBS!

27:49.460 --> 27:50.730
AND THEY'RE
UNDOCUMENTED.

27:50.770 --> 27:52.630
-THIS IS SUCH BULLSHIT.
-I --

27:52.670 --> 27:54.370
[ SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYS ]

27:54.400 --> 27:55.770
I NEED TO SEE<i> YOUR</i>
PAPERS, AS WELL.

27:55.800 --> 27:58.970
NO, WAIT. HE'S A PHYSICIAN
ASSISTANT AT A HOSPITAL!

27:59.010 --> 28:00.470
CHARLEY, IT'S FINE.

28:00.510 --> 28:02.610
THIS IS NOT
THE FIRST TIME.

28:02.640 --> 28:04.910
-SEÑORA.
-IGNACIO?

28:04.950 --> 28:07.710
IGNACIO, I WILL FIND YOU
AN ATTORNEY,<i> UN ABOGADO.</i>

28:07.750 --> 28:09.450
WHATEVER YOU NEED.
I'LL -- I'LL BE ON IT.

28:09.480 --> 28:11.550
JUST HOLD ON!

28:11.590 --> 28:13.950
UH, DETAIN THE FATHER
AND THE OLDEST BOY.

28:13.990 --> 28:15.190
YOUNGEST TWO ARE
AMERICAN CITIZENS.

28:15.220 --> 28:16.220
NO. NO!

28:16.260 --> 28:17.420
-ALL RIGHT, LET'S GO!
-NO, JUST --

28:17.460 --> 28:18.820
<i> -NO.</i>
<i> -NO NOS DEJES SOLO.</i>

28:18.860 --> 28:20.560
<i> -CáLMATE,</i> JOAQUIN.
-HEY HEY HEY HEY HEY HEY HEY.

28:20.590 --> 28:21.890
TAKE CARE OF YOUR
LITTLE BROTHER.

28:21.930 --> 28:23.600
PLEASE, CALL MY WIFE.

28:23.630 --> 28:24.800
LET HER KNOW
I'M BEING DETAINED.

28:24.830 --> 28:27.000
SHE NEEDS TO COME GET
JOAQUIN AND DANTE.

28:27.030 --> 28:29.330
I LOVE YOU, MI'JO!
IT'S GONNA BE OKAY.

28:29.370 --> 28:30.540
I LOVE YOU!

28:30.570 --> 28:33.640
♪♪

28:35.610 --> 28:36.580
I DON'T KNOW
HOW PEOPLE LIKE YOU

28:36.610 --> 28:38.140
LIVE WITH YOURSELVES.

28:38.180 --> 28:40.480
WELL, I'M DOIN'
JUST FINE.

28:40.510 --> 28:42.750
'SIDES, IT'S
OUT OF MY HANDS.

28:42.780 --> 28:44.320
AS SOON AS THOSE UNDOCS
ARE PROCESSED,

28:44.350 --> 28:45.380
THEY'RE GONNA BE PUT
ON THAT BUS

28:45.420 --> 28:47.450
AND TRANSPORTED
TO A DETENTION FACILITY.

28:47.490 --> 28:48.520
AND YOU OUGHTA
BE HAPPY

28:48.560 --> 28:49.520
I'M NOT SHUTTIN'
DOWN<i> YOUR</i> MILL

28:49.560 --> 28:51.660
FOR RUNNIN'
AN UNSANCTIONED CLINIC.

28:51.690 --> 28:53.890
WE'RE WORKING WITH THE
FARMWORKER HEALTH NETWORK.

28:53.930 --> 28:56.830
EVERY VOLUNTEER, DOCTOR,
AND NURSE WAS LICENSED

28:56.860 --> 28:59.570
AND OUR HEALTHCARE
WAS LEGAL, SO DON'T TRY ME.

28:59.600 --> 29:01.070
THOSE PEOPLE DON'T
BELONG IN SAINT JO.

29:01.100 --> 29:02.530
ACCORDING TO WHOM?!

29:02.570 --> 29:04.400
THE LANDRYS?

29:04.440 --> 29:06.000
I KNOW THEY CALLED IN
THE TIP.

29:06.040 --> 29:07.770
ARE YOU SAYING THEY
CALLED ICE ON<i> THEMSELVES?</i>

29:07.810 --> 29:09.410
SAM LANDRY LOST THREE
OF HIS BEST FARMHANDS

29:09.440 --> 29:10.880
ON THAT RAID.

29:10.910 --> 29:12.780
WELL, IF IT WASN'T
THE LANDRYS,

29:12.810 --> 29:14.350
THEN WHO DID THIS?

29:14.380 --> 29:16.010
IT'S HARD TO SAY.

29:16.050 --> 29:18.120
BUT I CAN TELL
YOU THIS:

29:18.150 --> 29:19.990
WHEN YOU CLOSED DOWN
OUR PRISON,

29:20.020 --> 29:21.350
YOU MADE MORE
ENEMIES IN A DAY

29:21.390 --> 29:24.360
THAN I MADE
IN A LIFETIME.

29:24.390 --> 29:25.690
GAL, YOU AIN'T POPULAR.

29:25.730 --> 29:27.490
[ MELANCHOLY TUNE PLAYS ]

29:27.530 --> 29:31.230
♪♪

29:31.270 --> 29:33.800
[ DOOR OPENS ]

29:33.830 --> 29:35.700
[ DOOR CLOSES,
ENGINE STARTS ]

29:35.740 --> 29:39.040
♪♪

29:39.070 --> 29:42.110
[<i> HIP HOP PLAYS</i> ]

29:42.140 --> 29:44.140
HEY, PROPS, BRUH,
FOR GETTIN' INKED UP

29:44.180 --> 29:45.410
IN HONOR OF ANT.

29:45.450 --> 29:46.980
YEAH, MAN.
I JUST --

29:47.010 --> 29:49.950
I WANT HIM TO KNOW THAT WE
DIDN'T FORGET ABOUT HIM.

29:49.980 --> 29:52.220
WELL, WHAT YOU NEED TO DO IS
SLOW DOWN ON THE DRINKIN'.

29:52.250 --> 29:53.950
THAT ALCOHOL WAS
FOR NUMBIN' THE PAIN,

29:53.990 --> 29:55.120
NOT GETTIN' DRUNK.

29:55.160 --> 29:58.820
YEAH, I COULD
BARELY FEEL IT.

29:58.860 --> 30:01.130
-AW, MAN, HE'S MESSED UP.
-MNH-MNH.

30:01.160 --> 30:02.690
AYE, YOU GONNA
THROW UP, MAN?

30:02.730 --> 30:04.260
-MM. MNH-MNH.
-OKAY, YOU KNOW WHAT?

30:04.300 --> 30:05.630
LET'S JUST GET HIM
TO THE BATHROOM

30:05.670 --> 30:06.830
BEFORE WE
ALL REGRET IT.

30:06.870 --> 30:08.030
NO-O.

30:08.070 --> 30:09.940
I'M FINE.

30:09.970 --> 30:10.940
SURE YOU ARE.

30:10.970 --> 30:12.470
COME ON.

30:12.510 --> 30:13.810
[laughs] YOU KNOW,
I LOVE YOU GUYS.

30:13.840 --> 30:15.510
-ONE STEP AT A TIME, BRUH.
-RIGHT.

30:15.540 --> 30:16.710
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

30:18.680 --> 30:20.110
HE SAY SOMETHING YET?

30:20.150 --> 30:21.780
NOTHING.

30:21.820 --> 30:23.920
JUST CRIED HIMSELF
TO SLEEP.

30:27.760 --> 30:28.790
I'LL BE BACK
IN THE MORNING

30:28.820 --> 30:32.090
TO CHECK ON HIM,
FIRST THING.

30:32.130 --> 30:33.560
HE COULD WAKE UP
IN THE NIGHT

30:33.590 --> 30:35.760
AND START
ASKING QUESTIONS.

30:35.800 --> 30:37.130
AND, HONESTLY,
RALPH ANGEL,

30:37.160 --> 30:38.300
I DON'T HAVE

30:38.330 --> 30:40.700
THE KIND AND GENTLE
THINGS TO SAY TO HIM.

30:40.730 --> 30:41.970
I KNOW.

30:49.140 --> 30:52.580
YOU'RE NOT...FURIOUS.

30:52.610 --> 30:55.110
IF IT'S WHAT I THINK
IT IS, THEN, YEAH.

30:55.150 --> 30:56.950
I'M MAD.

30:56.980 --> 30:58.920
FEEL BETRAYED.

30:58.950 --> 31:01.990
LIKE I CAN'T SHAKE
MY PAST.

31:02.020 --> 31:04.120
FARM DON'T MATTER.

31:04.160 --> 31:05.660
PAROLE ENDING
DON'T MATTER.

31:05.690 --> 31:07.890
♪♪

31:07.930 --> 31:09.230
PERSON THAT MATTER
MOST TO ME

31:09.260 --> 31:12.830
GOT A STAIN ON HIM,
'CAUSE OF<i> MY</i> CHOICES.

31:12.870 --> 31:14.770
NO.

31:14.800 --> 31:17.070
THE CHOICES<i> I</i> MADE.

31:17.100 --> 31:18.970
YEAH, WELL,
A LOT HAPPENED.

31:19.010 --> 31:20.240
WE BOTH PLAYED
OUR PART.

31:20.270 --> 31:24.040
♪♪

31:24.080 --> 31:25.580
ALL THAT MATTER
RIGHT NOW IS BLUE.

31:25.610 --> 31:31.180
♪♪

31:31.220 --> 31:33.190
WHY DID YOU STOP WRITING?

31:33.220 --> 31:35.690
OH, I STILL WRITE.

31:35.720 --> 31:36.920
AS I GET OLDER,
IT BECOMES

31:36.960 --> 31:38.290
INCREASINGLY MORE
IMPORTANT FOR ME

31:38.330 --> 31:40.190
TO MENTOR
THE NEXT GENERATION.

31:40.230 --> 31:41.330
HMM.

31:41.360 --> 31:42.630
YOU KNOW,
THERE WAS A TIME

31:42.660 --> 31:45.130
I THOUGHT<i> YOU</i> WOULD BE
MY GREATEST LEGACY.

31:45.170 --> 31:47.230
ACADEMIA WASN'T FOR ME.

31:47.270 --> 31:48.570
IT'S NOT
FOR ANY OF US.

31:48.600 --> 31:50.070
YOU KNOW, WE

31:50.100 --> 31:52.240
DO WHAT THE WORK DEMANDS.
WE ADAPT.

31:52.270 --> 31:54.040
OR NOT.

31:54.070 --> 31:57.580
I CHOSE TO WRITE
ABOUT PEOPLE, NOT THEORIES.

31:57.610 --> 32:00.280
I SET YOU UP FOR
INTELLECTUAL GREATNESS,

32:00.310 --> 32:02.980
NOT MEDIOCRITY IN THE FORM
OF A TELL-ALL BOOK.

32:03.020 --> 32:04.980
IT'S JUST US NOW.

32:05.020 --> 32:07.450
NO AUDIENCES
TO PERFORM FOR.

32:07.490 --> 32:09.620
YOU CAN ADMIT MY BOOK
WAS MORE THAN THAT.

32:09.660 --> 32:12.420
AND YOU ARE CAPABLE
OF SO MUCH MORE!

32:12.460 --> 32:15.290
COMING HERE
WAS A BIG MISTAKE.

32:15.330 --> 32:17.500
ONE LINE.

32:17.530 --> 32:20.230
THAT'S ALL YOU INCLUDED
IN YOUR BOOK.

32:20.270 --> 32:22.270
SOME VAGUE REFERENCE

32:22.300 --> 32:23.570
ABOUT A PROFESSOR BACK
AT TULANE

32:23.600 --> 32:25.570
WHO HELPED YOU
UNDERSTAND PATRIARCHY?

32:25.610 --> 32:27.910
SO, HUMILIATING ME ON STAGE,

32:27.940 --> 32:30.040
THAT WAS ABOUT ME NOT
ACKNOWLEDGING YOU IN MY BOOK?

32:30.080 --> 32:31.280
ONE LINE

32:31.310 --> 32:32.540
[crying] IS WORSE THAN
NO MENTION AT ALL,

32:32.580 --> 32:34.410
BECAUSE IT MEANS
THAT YOU THOUGHT

32:34.450 --> 32:36.080
ABOUT INCLUDING ME
AND THEN YOU MADE

32:36.120 --> 32:38.520
A CONSCIOUS
DECISION NOT TO.

32:38.550 --> 32:40.450
WHY IS THAT?

32:40.490 --> 32:44.160
IS IT BECAUSE YOU
NEVER THINK OF ME?

32:44.190 --> 32:47.860
'CAUSE I DON'T
BELIEVE THAT.

32:47.900 --> 32:50.260
WHAT ABOUT ALL THE TIME
THAT WE SPENT TOGETHER?

32:50.300 --> 32:52.260
♪♪

32:52.300 --> 32:54.000
WHAT ABOUT THE SUMMER

32:54.030 --> 32:55.130
IN ITALY...

32:55.170 --> 32:58.040
♪♪

32:58.070 --> 33:01.570
WHEN I COULD MAKE YOU
SAY MY NAME?

33:01.610 --> 33:03.480
AND I COULD MAKE YOU
SCREAM MINE?

33:03.510 --> 33:04.740
♪♪

33:04.780 --> 33:06.650
I REMEMBER THOSE DAYS.

33:06.680 --> 33:08.180
FONDLY.

33:08.220 --> 33:12.180
♪ HAVE YOU EVER SEEN ♪

33:12.220 --> 33:14.920
♪ I WISHED FOR BETTER ♪

33:14.960 --> 33:22.030
♪♪

33:24.010 --> 33:26.050
MMM, AS BEAUTIFUL

33:26.080 --> 33:28.720
AND AS STRONG
AS I REMEMBER.

33:28.750 --> 33:31.020
MMM.

33:31.060 --> 33:33.290
I CAN'T BELIEVE I'M HERE.

33:33.320 --> 33:37.490
WELL, IS IT REALLY
THAT SURPRISING?

33:37.530 --> 33:39.330
I THINK, IN THE BACK
OF BOTH OF OUR MINDS,

33:39.360 --> 33:41.830
WE ALWAYS KNEW
WE'D MEET UP AGAIN.

33:41.870 --> 33:42.960
MM.

33:43.000 --> 33:45.500
HOW LONG ARE YOU
IN NEW YORK?

33:45.540 --> 33:47.570
TOMORROW'S MY LAST DAY.

33:47.600 --> 33:50.170
THEN I MOVE ON TO BOSTON,
CHICAGO, ATLANTA,

33:50.210 --> 33:52.070
AND BATON ROUGE.

33:52.110 --> 33:53.980
THAT'S A SHAME.

33:54.010 --> 33:56.340
I WAS HOPING THAT WE
COULD CATCH UP.

33:56.380 --> 33:59.010
HM.

33:59.050 --> 34:00.450
YOU KNOW, I<i> COULD</i>
COME WITH YOU

34:00.480 --> 34:02.080
ON YOUR NEXT STOP.

34:02.120 --> 34:04.090
[laughing]
DON'T YOU HAVE CLASSES?

34:04.120 --> 34:06.320
MY GRADUATE STUDENTS
CAN COVER THEM.

34:06.360 --> 34:08.120
♪♪

34:08.160 --> 34:14.130
IT'D BE FUN TO SPEND
MORE TIME WITH YOU.

34:14.160 --> 34:15.560
JUST LIKE
THE OLD DAYS.

34:15.600 --> 34:21.070
♪♪

34:21.110 --> 34:22.200
THANKS FOR COMING BY.

34:22.240 --> 34:23.670
UH, CAN I GET YOU
A GLASS OF WINE OR...?

34:23.710 --> 34:24.910
OH, NO. I'M GOOD.

34:24.940 --> 34:27.340
THANK YOU. BUT I'M SURE
<i>YOU</i> COULD USE A GLASS.

34:27.380 --> 34:30.410
I HEARD ABOUT THE ICE
RAID AT YOUR MILL.

34:30.450 --> 34:32.150
[ SIGH ]

34:32.180 --> 34:34.720
THEY JUST TORE
A FAMILY APART.

34:34.750 --> 34:36.720
IGNACIO'S BEEN PART
OF OUR BUSINESS

34:36.750 --> 34:38.790
FOR YEARS, NOW,
AND I-I --

34:38.820 --> 34:40.290
I COULDN'T HELP HIM.

34:40.320 --> 34:42.220
I KNOW.

34:42.260 --> 34:44.130
IT'S DISGUSTING.

34:44.160 --> 34:47.000
BUT, I ALSO HEARD
THAT YOU HAD

34:47.030 --> 34:48.360
YOUR P.I. FRIEND VICKY

34:48.400 --> 34:50.400
GOING THROUGH OLD
LAND RECORDS.

34:50.430 --> 34:52.730
NOW, IF THAT
INFORMATION GOT TO ME,

34:52.770 --> 34:55.100
IT GOT TO OTHERS,
AS WELL.

34:55.140 --> 34:58.140
SO, THE RAID'S A MESSAGE.

34:58.180 --> 34:59.340
SOMEONE'S TRYING
TO STOP ME

34:59.380 --> 35:02.110
FROM ASKING QUESTIONS
ABOUT THE NEW HIGHWAY.

35:02.150 --> 35:04.910
DOES SAINT THOMAS<i> KNOW</i>
THE LANDRYS ARE TRYING

35:04.950 --> 35:06.310
TO MOVE THE HIGHWAY
TO SAINT JO?

35:06.350 --> 35:08.280
THEY KNOW<i> SOMEONE'S</i>
TRYING TO TAKE

35:08.320 --> 35:09.450
THE HIGHWAY FROM THEM

35:09.490 --> 35:11.220
AND THEY'RE
NOT HAPPY ABOUT IT.

35:11.260 --> 35:12.990
I MEAN, WITHOUT IT,
THEY LOSE THE TOURISTS

35:13.020 --> 35:15.490
AND TURN
INTO A GHOST TOWN.

35:15.530 --> 35:17.760
HOW LONG UNTIL THEY PLAN
TO BREAK GROUND?

35:17.790 --> 35:21.060
-OH, CHARLEY, I --
-HOW LONG?

35:21.100 --> 35:23.500
FIVE MONTHS,
MAYBE SIX.

35:23.530 --> 35:24.570
IT'S BEING
FAST-TRACKED.

35:24.600 --> 35:27.340
SIX MONTHS?

35:27.370 --> 35:29.170
THAT CAN'T HAPPEN.

35:29.210 --> 35:33.480
WE HAVE TO STOP IT OR --
OR FIND A WAY TO SLOW IT DOWN.

35:33.510 --> 35:35.380
YOU COULD TEAM UP
WITH THE PEOPLE

35:35.410 --> 35:36.850
OF SAINT THOMAS,

35:36.880 --> 35:38.550
GATHER ENOUGH SIGNATURES
TO PUT THE HIGHWAY

35:38.580 --> 35:40.620
ON THE BALLOT
IN<i> BOTH</i> PARISHES

35:40.650 --> 35:42.250
AND LET
THE PEOPLE DECIDE.

35:42.290 --> 35:44.620
IT'S A LONG SHOT,
BUT, IF YOU CAN EXPOSE

35:44.660 --> 35:47.120
THE LANDRYS'
LOBBYING EFFORT,

35:47.160 --> 35:50.460
MIGHT HAVE A CHANCE.

35:50.490 --> 35:51.960
YOU COULD ALSO --
-RUN FOR COUNCIL

35:52.000 --> 35:53.630
AGAINST JACOB BOUDREAUX.

35:53.660 --> 35:55.530
♪♪

35:55.570 --> 35:58.000
THE HIGHWAY IS COMING,
BUT IT'S THE CITY COUNCIL

35:58.040 --> 36:01.140
WHO DECIDES<i> EXACTLY</i>
WHERE IT GOES.

36:01.170 --> 36:02.800
IF YOU CAN GET COUNCIL
TO MOVE THE HIGHWAY

36:02.840 --> 36:04.270
JUST FIVE MILES WEST --

36:04.310 --> 36:07.180
THEN MOST OF THE FARMERS'
LAND WOULD BE SPARED,

36:07.210 --> 36:09.110
INCLUDING MY DADDY'S LAND.

36:09.150 --> 36:10.750
BUT YOU NEED TO BE
CAREFUL, CHARLEY.

36:10.780 --> 36:12.350
IF YOU DECIDE TO RUN,

36:12.380 --> 36:13.620
YOU'LL DISCOVER
THE LANDRYS

36:13.650 --> 36:16.120
ARE JUST THE<i> TIP</i>
OF THE SPEAR.

36:16.150 --> 36:18.450
WHATEVER THE LANDRYS
AND THEIR FRIENDS THROW AT ME,

36:18.490 --> 36:19.620
I'LL BE READY.

36:19.660 --> 36:21.390
IF YOU DO THIS,
YOU BETTER BE.

36:21.430 --> 36:24.090
FILING DEADLINE TO RUN
FOR COUNCIL IS IN TWO DAYS.

36:24.130 --> 36:26.930
♪♪

36:26.960 --> 36:28.560
YOU THINK
I'D HAVE A SHOT?

36:28.600 --> 36:30.430
[ KNOCK AT DOOR,
DOOR OPENS ]

36:30.470 --> 36:31.970
HEY. I DIDN'T KNOW
THAT YOU WERE --

36:32.000 --> 36:34.000
OH, MY GOD. WHAT HAPPENED?
ARE YOU HURT?!

36:34.040 --> 36:35.240
NO, I JUST --

36:38.410 --> 36:39.980
IT'S -- IT'S JUST
A LITTLE TATTOO.

36:45.350 --> 36:47.880
HAVE YOU BEEN DRINKING?

36:47.920 --> 36:51.020
I DIDN'T MEAN TO GET
DRUNK. I WAS JUST --

36:51.050 --> 36:53.820
I JUST TOOK A FEW SIPS
TO NUMB THE PAIN.

36:53.860 --> 36:57.190
YOU'RE 17.

36:57.230 --> 36:59.890
TOO YOUNG FOR A TATTOO
AND DEFINITELY

36:59.930 --> 37:01.060
TOO YOUNG TO BE DRINKING.

37:01.100 --> 37:02.460
MA. COME ON.

37:02.500 --> 37:03.730
MICAH!

37:03.770 --> 37:05.130
YOU'RE STARTING
TO MAKE CHOICES

37:05.170 --> 37:06.670
THAT YOU'LL HAVE TO LIVE WITH
FOR THE REST OF YOUR LIFE.

37:06.700 --> 37:07.940
ARE YOU -- ARE YOU EVEN
THINKING ABOUT THAT?

37:07.970 --> 37:09.370
IT'S A TATTOO!

37:09.410 --> 37:10.810
<i> EVERYBODY</i>
DOES IT NOW.

37:10.840 --> 37:12.340
OKAY.

37:12.380 --> 37:13.580
I GET IT.

37:13.610 --> 37:15.040
YOU'RE A YOUNG MAN NOW.

37:15.080 --> 37:16.910
THE ROAD AHEAD IS
COMPLICATED FOR ALL OF US,

37:16.950 --> 37:22.120
BUT, FOR YOU, IT'S --

37:22.150 --> 37:23.550
IF YOU WON'T LISTEN
TO ME ANYMORE,

37:23.590 --> 37:25.020
JUST LET ME KNOW
WHO YOU WILL LISTEN TO.

37:25.060 --> 37:26.890
MA, I<i> DO</i> LISTEN
TO YOU.

37:26.920 --> 37:28.590
[ SLAM ]

37:28.630 --> 37:37.900
♪♪

37:37.930 --> 37:45.010
♪♪

37:45.040 --> 37:50.180
♪ TAKE MY HAND AND SEE ♪

37:50.210 --> 37:53.420
♪ WHERE WE COULD GO ♪

37:53.450 --> 37:55.320
♪ WILL YOU TAKE ♪

37:55.350 --> 37:58.490
♪ THE LEAP? ♪

37:58.520 --> 38:02.420
♪ LEAVE THE FEAR BEHIND ♪

38:02.460 --> 38:04.290
♪ AND ♪

38:04.330 --> 38:08.400
♪ LET ME KNOW ♪

38:08.430 --> 38:12.900
♪ NOW ♪

38:12.940 --> 38:18.470
♪♪

38:18.510 --> 38:19.670
READY TO TELL US
WHAT HAPPENED, BUDDY?

38:19.710 --> 38:22.040
♪♪

38:22.080 --> 38:23.810
MY FRIEND MARCUS SAID

38:23.850 --> 38:25.350
YOU'RE NOT
MY REAL DADDY.

38:25.380 --> 38:28.420
[ CRYING ]

38:28.450 --> 38:30.520
YEAH, WELL,
MARCUS WRONG.

38:30.550 --> 38:33.520
-[SNIFFLE]
-'CAUSE I AM YOUR DADDY,

38:33.560 --> 38:36.090
IN ALL THE WAYS
THAT MATTER, JUST...

38:36.130 --> 38:39.190
JUST NOT IN THE
BIOLOGICAL WAY.

38:39.230 --> 38:41.100
WHAT'S "BIOLOGICAL" MEAN?

38:41.130 --> 38:42.760
JUST MEAN THAT

38:42.800 --> 38:44.830
PART OF A MOMMY,
PART OF A DADDY

38:44.870 --> 38:46.400
COME TOGETHER TO

38:46.440 --> 38:48.440
MAKE A BABY,

38:48.470 --> 38:50.240
THAT'S ALL.

38:50.270 --> 38:52.640
I THOUGHT YOU<i> WERE</i>
A PART OF ME, POPS.

38:52.680 --> 38:56.010
♪♪

38:56.050 --> 38:57.910
IS THAT WHY I LOOK
DIFFERENT THAN YOU?

38:57.950 --> 39:00.650
♪♪

39:00.680 --> 39:01.680
[ SOB ]

39:01.720 --> 39:03.850
IT DON'T MATTER
WHAT WE LOOK LIKE.

39:03.890 --> 39:06.760
HALF OF MY SOUL
INSIDE YOU.

39:06.790 --> 39:09.620
THAT MEAN OUR
HEARTBEAT THE SAME.

39:09.660 --> 39:12.890
LOOK.

39:12.930 --> 39:15.130
FEEL THAT?

39:15.170 --> 39:16.400
YEAH?
-[SNIFFLE]

39:16.430 --> 39:18.700
ALRIGHT.

39:18.740 --> 39:20.470
FEEL THAT?

39:20.500 --> 39:22.040
YEAH?

39:22.070 --> 39:23.200
YEAH.

39:23.240 --> 39:24.510
THAT'S THE KIND
OF FATHER AND SON

39:24.540 --> 39:26.910
WE ARE,
HEART TO HEART.

39:26.940 --> 39:29.340
I CHOSE YOU.

39:29.380 --> 39:31.880
I CHOSE TO BE
YOUR DADDY.

39:31.920 --> 39:34.880
I CHOOSE TO TAKE
CARE OF YOU,

39:34.920 --> 39:37.350
HELP YOU WITH
YOUR HOMEWORK...

39:37.390 --> 39:38.620
[ HITCHING SOBS ]

39:38.660 --> 39:41.290
...TUCK YOU INTO BED.

39:41.320 --> 39:45.090
WHAT IF YOU CHOOSE
SOMEONE ELSE, ONE DAY,

39:45.130 --> 39:48.000
ANOTHER BOY, OR GIRL?

39:48.030 --> 39:50.530
THAT'LL NEVER HAPPEN.

39:50.570 --> 39:53.200
LONG AS MY HEART
IS BEATIN', BLUE,

39:53.240 --> 39:58.070
IMMA BE YOUR DADDY,
'CAUSE I CHOSE<i> YOU.</i>

39:58.110 --> 40:00.610
YOU CHOSE ME,
TOO, RIGHT?

40:00.640 --> 40:01.880
YEAH.

40:01.910 --> 40:03.810
[ CRYING ]

40:03.850 --> 40:05.250
IT'S ALRIGHT.

40:05.280 --> 40:06.550
IT'S ALRIGHT.

40:06.580 --> 40:09.550
[ CONTINUES CRYING ]

40:09.590 --> 40:15.290
♪♪

40:15.330 --> 40:17.360
ALRIGHT.

40:17.390 --> 40:20.030
IS THERE A PART
OF YOU IN ME?

40:20.060 --> 40:21.530
THERE IS.

40:21.570 --> 40:23.870
'CAUSE YOU'RE
MY BIOLOGICAL MOMMY?

40:23.900 --> 40:25.870
I AM.

40:25.900 --> 40:28.370
BUT EVEN IF I WASN'T,

40:28.410 --> 40:31.570
I WOULD STILL
CHOOSE<i> YOU,</i>

40:31.610 --> 40:34.980
A<i> HUNDRED</i> TIMES OVER.

40:35.010 --> 40:37.310
JUST LIKE
YOUR DADDY.

40:37.350 --> 40:39.150
♪ OOH OOH OOH OOH OOH ♪

40:39.180 --> 40:45.390
♪ NOW IS
THE HARD TIME ♪

40:45.420 --> 40:49.220
LOVE YOU.

40:49.260 --> 40:50.460
I LOVE YOU.

40:50.490 --> 40:53.360
♪♪

40:53.400 --> 40:55.330
♪ OOH OOH OOH OOH OOH ♪

40:55.370 --> 40:58.500
♪ IF NOT NOW ♪

40:58.540 --> 41:01.300
♪ WHEN? ♪

41:01.340 --> 41:02.500
♪ FOR ME ♪

41:02.540 --> 41:05.440
♪ TO SEE ♪

